# Lean agent mode (ND-Portfolio)

Default to the cheap path. Planning and review live in **Opus terminal** — see `composer-orchestration.mdc`.

## Do NOT use (unless user explicitly asks)

- **All MCP tools** — browser, Vercel, Stripe, Prisma, app-control, etc.
- **Planner / verifier / reviewer subagents** in Cursor — user runs **Claude Opus 4.8** in terminal; Composer supplies paste-ready prompts.
- **Browser automation** — user verifies UI manually at `http://localhost:3001`.
- **Repeated terminal probes** — if shell fails once, ask user to run commands and paste output.

## DO use

- **Composer as orchestrator** — Opus prompts for plan/review; implement after user pastes Opus output.
- **`/implementer` subagent** for multi-file phase work when appropriate.
- Read **only** the active phase file + latest handoff (paths in `CLAUDE.md`).
- **One phase per chat** when possible.
- User runs: `npm run lint`, `npm run build`, `npm run dev`.
- Append results to the phase execution log; handoff only at session end or phase close.

## Phased-workflow

- Follow phase files in `docs/0N_*.md` (authored via Opus terminal, implemented in Cursor).
- Do not reload full skills corpus every turn — phase file + `docs/00_plan.md` only.
- No commit unless user explicitly asks.

## Content rules (unchanged)

- Owner-editable content only in `src/content/*.ts`.
- Append photos/projects at bottom → newest-first render.
